## 11. Summary & Investment Conclusions

### Model Architecture
This portfolio is built on three pillars:
1. **Market equilibrium** (prior): avoids extreme Markowitz concentration
2. **Active macro views** (from Market Insight letter): translates qualitative views into quantitative signals
3. **Optimisation with constraints**: max 25% per asset enforces genuine diversification

### Views Implemented
| View | Rationale from Letter |
|---|---|
| India > Japan +3% | Young demographics, digitalization, long-term structural growth |
| Healthcare > World Quality +2% | Indirect AI beneficiary, drug discovery acceleration |
| Euro IG > US Treasuries +1.5% | Overweight euro duration, IG over HY |
| Infrastructure absolute +8% | AI energy capex, real assets structural demand |

### Key Limitations
- Views are subjective — model output is only as good as the macro analysis
- Omega calibration (view uncertainty) significantly affects results
- Historical covariance may not capture regime changes
- No transaction costs or liquidity constraints modelled

### Possible Extensions
- Dynamic BL with rolling window views
- GARCH-DCC for time-varying covariance
- Risk parity as alternative weighting scheme
- Factor attribution (Fama-French, Barra)

